Here are Some Basic command which we use in Linux.

1. cd :- This command is to change directory
   ex: we have some Directory called Directory_1 , Directory_2 , Linux , Home, etc
       use cd Linux so will jump into Linux directory.
cd – returns to the current user’s home directory.
cd .. – moves a directory up.
cd – – goes back to the previous directory.

2. pwd :- To check the full path of your current working directory, use the pwd commandit shows the present working directory
	ex:- pwd [options]

3. ls :-  The ls command lists the content of a folder, including files and directories
	ex:- ls [options] [directory_or_path] 

4.mkdir command :- The mkdir command lets you create one or multiple directories. 
5.rmdir command :- Run rmdir to delete empty directories in your Linux system.  
6.rm command :- The rm command deletes files from a directory.
7.cp command :- Use the cp command to copy files from your current directory to another folder.

